<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014-06-10</DATELINE><TITLE>China Declares Global State of Emergency: An Urgent Telegram from Taihu</TITLE><BODY>May 18th, 2013, China’s 4th most powerful politician, Yu Zhengsheng, Chairman of the National Committee of the CPPCC (Chinese People’s Political Consultative Conference) opened the Second Conference of the (carbon-neutralized) Taihu World Cultural Forum in Hangzhou, a city 1 h by speed train southwest of Shanghai. “What kind of a planet will we leave to our descendants? This is an urgent subject which deserves the collective attention of the whole world,” he said with a sincere air of emergency.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>